JOHANNESBURG – Former police minister Fikile Mbalula has resigned from Parliament. This was confirmed through a statement by the office of the ANC Chief Whip in the National Assembly. Mbalula got the chop during President Cyril Ramaphosa’s Cabinet reshuffle in late February. READ: I was prepared for redeployment: Mbalula The former minister’s resignation is effective from 26 February 2018, the statement by Jackson Mthembu’s office said. “While comrade Mbalula’s departure from Parliament will leave a void, we derive satisfaction from the knowledge that he will continue serving the movement as the ANC’s Head of Elections towards the 2019 General Elections campaign,” the statement added. READ: Mbalula appointed to head ANC’s elections machinery Mbalula's old post was taken over by former police commissioner General Bheki Cele. eNCA